## One line

RFE = `precision_flow`'s already-banked **transcendental-flow** successor. The new
build is **the transverse enclosure carried per precision-flow tick ("grape on the
vine") + a typed classifier of how that remainder behaves under refinement**, with
`boundary_straddling` and `bounded_transcendental_tail`-as-carried-grape as the only
two genuinely-new graded classes. Six of the eight proposed classes are *re-labels
of ratified results* and must be cited, not re-derived.

## What is genuinely new (the build)

1. **The carried object** — `RemainderFlowCell`: an exact precision-flow tick
   (skeleton value + Cella account) with a **certified transverse enclosure** (the
   transcendental remainder) and its diameter, evolving under refinement. The *pieces*
   exist (difference-tower H7 enclosures; the spine's typed transcendental enclosures);
   carrying the enclosure **on the precision-flow skeleton as a first-class object** is
   the new composition.
2. **The typed refinement-behaviour classifier** — one verdict surface over a remainder.
   No closed campaign emits this surface (cf. the I3 kit's NON-ASSEMBLY ruling — see
   the gate below).
3. **`boundary_straddling` as a graded class** — only *exhibits* exist today (the
   Newton terminal 2-cycle straddling √(2+√3), Arm M / atlas Facet E; the precision-flow
   parity-trap). Grading straddling **as a remainder class** is new (thin).
4. **`bounded_transcendental_tail` as a carried-and-decided grape** — the spine gives
   the enclosure machinery; carrying the tail *uninterpreted* and consuming it only when
   narrow enough to decide is a new composition, not a closed win.

